issues.description: The problem specification requires a constructor that initializes all five attributes in the order shown in the UML (lectureName, numberOfInscribedStudents, numberOfGuestStudents, numberOfLecturers, numberOfTutors), but the template’s Lecture class provides a stub constructor with only three parameters (lectureName, numberOfInscribedStudents, numberOfGuestStudents). This mismatch will confuse students about which parameters are needed and their correct order.
issues.suggested_fix: Update the constructor stub in the template to accept and initialize all five attributes in the proper order: (String lectureName, int numberOfInscribedStudents, int numberOfGuestStudents, int numberOfLecturers, int numberOfTutors).
